Dear Monday Bar family, The Jubilee Cruise lineup October 6-8 is now complete with over 50 djs.. and one mc. And we are proud to announce that one third of them are performing for the very first time at Monday Bar. Below is our poster that goes up next week. You can find presentation of all djs with images and links on our cruise page: https://www.mondaybar.com/lineup-60th-jubilee-cruise <https://www.mondaybar.com/lineup-60th-jubilee-cruise?ss_source=sscampaigns&ss_campaign_id=64a452a5bfbe512eb65956db&ss_email_id=64a456a0d3a8a220b22c602a&ss_campaign_name=The+Jubilee+Cruise+lineup+is+now+complete%21&ss_campaign_sent_date=2023-07-04T17%3A28%3A59Z> Booking of cabins have now been open for a month, so don’t wait too long to reserve your preferred cabin type while they’re still available. Monday Bar crew 🌻 Who would have guessed over 20 years ago that we would sail together for the 60th time on the Baltic sea! We’ll, here we are, and it’s time again to board the best party ship of the Tallink-Silja fleet, M/S Baltic Queen. The cruise is in the beginning of October, but thanks to an outside sun deck partly covered with a roof and wind shield we should be able to enjoy a daytime party on deck while in port in Tallinn on Saturday. MONDAY BAR CRUISE No 60 JUBILEE Friday-Sunday October 6-8, 2023 (2 nights - 41h) M/S Baltic Queen Stockholm-Tallinn-Stockholm Cruise times Departure, Stockholm Tallink-Silja ferry terminal, Värtahamnen Friday, October 6, 17:30 (5:30 PM), local Swedish time Arrival, Tallinn Tallink D-terminal Saturday October 7, 10:45 (10:45 AM), local Estonian time (+1 hour) Departure, Tallinn Tallink D-terminal Saturday October 7, 18:00 (6 PM), local Estonian time (+1 hour) Arrival, Stockholm Tallink-Silja ferry terminal, Värtahamnen Sunday October 8, 10:30 (10:30 AM), local Swedish time Age limit: 18 years when boarding. Cabin prices starting at SEK 1420 per person CRUISE HOMEPAGE  <https://www.mondaybar.com/mondaybar-no-60-jubilee-cruise-2023?ss_source=sscampai